******************************************************************
    DESCRIPTION
******************************************************************

    This module provides a method to save and re-use configurations
    of the Primer Theme (http://drupal.ncsu.edu).

    The Primer Theme Manager module is an optional partner for the 
    Primer Theme. It only works with the Primer theme, and no others.
    
    
    

******************************************************************
    FEATURES
******************************************************************
    Save theme configurations locally for re-use
    
    Export theme configurations to share with other primer-themed 
    websites
    
    Export theme configurations to share with the Drupal service 
    administrator, who can make your configuration available to 
    everyone using the primer theme automatically.
    
    Import theme configurations that were exported by someone 
    else using this module
    
    Delete local theme configurations
    
    
    
    
******************************************************************
    CONFIGURATION
******************************************************************
    1. Install the module according to Drupal instructions
    2. Set permissions for "Administer Primer Manager"
    3. Access module options from 
        "Site Building" --> Primer Theme Manager
    
    
    Important: When applying or exporting the theme configuration, 
    these settings will be ignored.
        
